(578, 1, '2015-01-25 14:51:56', '2015-01-25 14:51:56', 'SJ choose SharePoint 2013 Online for upgrading their intranet and the new requirements set by the company. I worked closely with various stakeholders in SJ\'s organisation in order to communicate my the design and concept. My responsibility was to continuously inform these stakeholders throughout the project. As the project progressed, I took on the role of Product Owner and help the organization to establish requirements and prioritize the backlog created for the Scrum-based development team.\r\n<h3>Challanges:</h3>\r\nLarge company with many target groups. Complex environment that would work in a mobile  and an office environment. With all what that involves,  mental models, attention to what you are working with and external factors from a security perspective.\r\n<h3>Experience:</h3>\r\nDistinct and regular communication to the business and personas / reference groups. Greater responsibility in terms of requirements, Scrum and project management.\r\n<h3>Methods and processes:</h3>\r\nField studies, usability testing, focus group analysis, personas, scenarios, board meeting presentation, documentation and communication of the Board and management teams.\r\n<h3>Conclusion:</h3>\r\nAs a UX designer works with a variety of professional roles and stakeholders. It requires distinct and honest communication. Communicated in a way specific individual and professional roles can absorb it. You need to be flexible and give clear directions when the project is complex and demands are high.', 'SJ - intranet', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '464-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-25 14:51:56', '2015-01-25 14:51:56', '', 464, 'http://www.mikaeleng.se/464-revision-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(580, 1, '2015-01-25 15:05:03', '2015-01-25 15:05:03', 'One of my first assignments at HiQ was a new app for Mr Green in Germany. It is a app that is free to play, casino and other quick games in the app. The Challange was to make one single design framework for several different games with their own design interface. The app was developed in Russia and the UX/UI was developed in Sweden.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe app was built both for IOS and Android. we hade to take in consideration all the different sceen sizes, design guidelines and design patterns known by the users.', 'Skill games', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '460-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-25 15:05:03', '2015-01-25 15:05:03', '', 460, 'http://www.mikaeleng.se/460-revision-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(581, 1, '2015-01-25 15:06:26', '2015-01-25 15:06:26', 'Cambio wanted to create a new public website that was more communicative and modern. The site would be responsive and adapt to diffenrent screen sizes. Using a variety of internal workshops with the client and all the stakeholders at Cambio to generate an efficiency map with the different target groups and their needs. With the target groups mapped out I did interviews with the four main target groups. I performed usability tests and A / B tests for various interactive work flows to create the best user experience. We used SCRUM as project methodology where I also accounted for all requirements specification and testing.', 'Communicative company site', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '456-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-25 15:06:26', '2015-01-25 15:06:26', '', 456, 'http://www.mikaeleng.se/456-revision-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(582, 1, '2015-01-25 15:06:41', '2015-01-25 15:06:41', 'Wasa Kredit needed a new sales support tool for the different sales divisions which at the time had several different kinds of applications. I worked with Windows-specific interaction patterns and supported the rest of the development team with usability and information about user needs looked. I did several user interviews. I made continuous usability testing with users by producing a complex prototype in Axure and used the same tools to communicate interaction with the rest of the development team. I did A / B testing to ensure the system they used the best interaction patterns for the specific users\' mental model of the system.\r\n<h3>Challanges</h3>\r\nIn large, complex projects for heavy IT systems, it is important to find the right extent of the design experience and both work at a high overall level for stakeholders and detailed level with the development team. Merging two large, complex IT systems used by many different audiences was another challange. And developing the right design patterns for widespread audiences.\r\n<h3>Experince</h3>\r\nWorking in distint sprints with a clear scum methodology to iterate through design proposals with project team and stakeholders.\r\n<h3>Methods and processes</h3>\r\nField studies, A / B testing scenarios, Wireframes, White board, pencil and paper, efficiency mapping, task analyzes.\r\n<h3>Conclusion</h3>\r\nWhen you have a close contact with end users and can do a lot of user testing it is a good way to know your work is on the right track. You can base all your work on facts instead of feelings.', 'New Sale support tool', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '462-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-25 15:06:41', '2015-01-25 15:06:41', '', 462, 'http://www.mikaeleng.se/462-revision-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(583, 1, '2015-01-25 15:07:53', '2015-01-25 15:07:53', 'Through workshops with SLF and interviews with employees at the company, I built a new information architecture of the site. I cleaned up the existing website and structured all the information created over a long period of time. In various workshops and interviews, I made an efficiency map and came up with different target groups. Focusing the website content on these target groups made the website more usable . I built a complex prototype to visualize the functionality, infrastructure and user experience at the new site. The prototype was then used in the design and development phase.\r\n<h3>Challanges</h3>\r\nGeting the company to understand the use of target groups to focus the website and help the users find their needs so they will get a better experience.\r\n<h3>Experience</h3>\r\nMaking complex information structures visual for target groups and stakeholders. Geting them to understand the models and working close with the target groups.\r\n<h3>Conclusion</h3>\r\nBuilding an understanding for information architecture and target groups will help your communication with stakeholder. Get your stakeholders to participate in the workshops with target groups and card sorting meetings will make your job easier.', 'Doctors union website', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '375-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-25 15:07:53', '2015-01-25 15:07:53', '', 375, 'http://www.mikaeleng.se/375-revision-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(584, 1, '2015-01-25 15:08:26', '2015-01-25 15:08:26', 'Ett av mina längre projekt på Nordnet var Nordnets nya blogg. Den är utvecklad i WordPress och jag hade huvudansvar för kommunikationen med den externa webbyrån som utvecklade bloggen. Jag tillsammans med en Art Director tog fram själva konceptet och lösningsförslaget. Där jag stod för den interaktiva delarna och användabarhets-aspekten. För tydlig och snabb kommunikation med en webbyrå som befann sig i Finland byggde jag en <a href="http://share.axure.com/PKXFHS/Home.html" target="_blank">hi-fiprototyp i Axure</a> för att kunna diskutera och arbeta tillsammans över det långa avståndet. Samma prototyp användes också för att visa internt på Nordnet hur den nya blogportalen skulle se ut och fungera.\r\n\r\nOne of my major projects at Nordnet bank was developing their new blog site. The site was built in wordpress and had stakeholders in four different countries. I was in charge of the UX-design, communicating with the external web agency that developed the site. I also was in charge of the general concept and built a hifi-prototype to be able to communicate my ideas with the development team in Finland and the stakeholders at Nordnet.\r\n\r\nI developed target group analysis, intervjued users in four different countries and kept in contact and got feeback during the entire project time from them. I built personas and scenarios to get my message through to the development team so they understood the challanges the diffrent uses had in the different countries.', 'Blog site', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '342-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-25 15:08:26', '2015-01-25 15:08:26', '', 342, 'http://www.mikaeleng.se/342-revision-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(492, 1, '2014-12-15 12:36:32', '2014-12-15 12:36:32', 'Avito is Russia\'s largest web portal for classifieds. Avito wanted to create a better user experience for their service providers. Create a digital tool that their users could use as an everyday tool for their business. I did field studies on location in Russia and in-depth interviews and user tests with Russian users.\r\n\r\nChallanges \r\nTo understand and explore a new culture with different non-conscious interactions and mental models was one big challanges. Another challange was working with customers at a great distance and manage their expectations. To facilitate that I hade to give quick and detailed feedback as much as possible. I alos took on the role of UX Lead and worked with project planning, close customer contact, assign tasks and overall project management.\r\n\r\nExperience\r\nThe most important thing when working with international clients is to maintain frequent communication and pay extra attention to stakeholders expectations. While doing the interviewing users through an interpreter I must find clever ways to communicate without having to use the interpreter all the time. One can e.g. use scales to the user by pointing to a value on a scale answer a question.\r\n\r\nMethods and processes\r\nField studies, in-depth interviews, A/B tests, wireframes, Axure prototype, efficiency mapping, powerpoint presentations, documentation and communication to the board of directors.', 'Avito', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '458-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-12-15 12:36:32', '2014-12-15 12:36:32', '', 458, 'http://www.mikaeleng.se/458-revision-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(451, 1, '2014-12-04 22:53:23', '2014-12-04 22:53:23', 'Locomotiv jobbade med Miljöpartiet inför valet 2010. En del av kampanjen var en film som gick i de flesta tv-kanaler. Jag fick i uppgift att göra en digital videospelare för Miljöpartiets webbsida. Den använde streamingtjänstern Streamio men jag har även jobbat med QBrick i tidigare projekt. Det ni ser här är en progressiv spelare som inte streamar filmen från Streamios servrar. Annars fungerar den precis likadant.', 'Miljöpartiet', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '34-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-12-04 22:53:23', '2014-12-04 22:53:23', '', 34, 'http://192.168.1.4/mikaeleng/34-revision-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(456, 1, '2013-05-05 12:00:16', '2013-05-05 12:00:16', 'Cambio wanted to create a new public website that was more communicative and modern. The site would be responsive and adapt to diffenrent screen sizes. Using a variety of internal workshops with the client and all the stakeholders at Cambio to generate an efficiency map with the different target groups and their needs. With the target groups mapped out I did interviews with the four main target groups. I performed usability tests and A / B tests for various interactive work flows to create the best user experience. We used SCRUM as project methodology where I also accounted for all requirements specification and testing.', 'A responsive web site', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'a-responsive-web-site', '', '', '2015-04-01 21:59:29', '2015-04-01 21:59:29', '', 0, 'http://192.168.1.4/mikaeleng/?p=456', 0, 'post', '', 0),
