(462, 1, '2014-01-07 12:00:51', '2014-01-07 12:00:51', 'Wasa Kredit needed a new sales support tool for the different sales divisions which at the time had several different kinds of applications. I worked with Windows-specific interaction patterns and supported the rest of the development team with usability and information about user needs looked. I did several user interviews. I made continuous usability testing with users by producing a complex prototype in Axure and used the same tools to communicate interaction with the rest of the development team. I did A / B testing to ensure the system they used the best interaction patterns for the specific users\' mental model of the system.\r\n<h3>Challanges</h3>\r\nIn large, complex projects for heavy IT systems, it is important to find the right extent of the design experience and both work at a high overall level for stakeholders and detailed level with the development team. Merging two large, complex IT systems used by many different audiences was another challange. And developing the right design patterns for widespread audiences.\r\n<h3>Experince</h3>\r\nWorking in distint sprints with a clear scum methodology to iterate through design proposals with project team and stakeholders.\r\n<h3>Methods and processes</h3>\r\nField studies, A / B testing scenarios, Wireframes, White board, pencil and paper, efficiency mapping, task analyzes.\r\n<h3>Conclusion</h3>\r\nWhen you have a close contact with end users and can do a lot of user testing it is a good way to know your work is on the right track. You can base all your work on facts instead of feelings.', 'A new CRM tool', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'a-new-crm-tool', '', '', '2015-03-10 19:16:15', '2015-03-10 19:16:15', '', 0, 'http://192.168.1.4/mikaeleng/?p=462', 0, 'post', '', 0),
