(464, 1, '2015-01-03 12:00:11', '2015-01-03 12:00:11', 'SJ choose SharePoint 2013 Online for upgrading their intranet and the new requirements set by the company. I worked closely with various stakeholders in SJ\'s organisation in order to communicate the design and concept. My responsibility was to continuously inform these stakeholders throughout the project. As the project progressed, I took on the role of Product Owner and help the organization to establish requirements and prioritize the backlog created for the Scrum-based development team.\r\n<h3>Challanges:</h3>\r\nLarge company with many target groups. Complex environment that would work in a mobile  and an destop environment. I worked with mental models, attention to what you are working with and external factors from a security perspective.\r\n<h3>Experience:</h3>\r\nDistinct and regular communication to the business and personas / reference groups. Greater responsibility in terms of requirements, the Scrum process and production management.\r\n<h3>Methods and processes:</h3>\r\nField studies, usability testing, focus group analysis, personas, scenarios, board meeting presentation, documentation and communicating the internal information to the Board and management teams.\r\n<h3>Conclusion:</h3>\r\nAs a UX designer works with a variety of professional roles and stakeholders. It requires distinct and honest communication. Communicated in a way specific individual and professional roles can absorb it. You need to be flexible and give clear directions when the project is complex and demands are high.', 'Intranet', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'sj-intranet', '', '', '2015-07-23 19:19:00', '2015-07-23 19:19:00', '', 0, 'http://192.168.1.4/mikaeleng/?p=464', 0, 'post', '', 0),
