(496, 1, '2014-12-15 13:13:21', '2014-12-15 13:13:21', 'Wasa Kredit needed a new sales support which was a common system for the different sales divisions which at the time had several different kinds of applications. Mikael worked with Windows-specific interaction patterns and supported the rest of the development team with usability and information about user needs looked. Michael had frequent communication with users of various existing systems to while working meeting of usability. Michael made continuous usability testing with users by producing a complex prototype in Axure and used the same tools to communicate interaction with the rest of the development team. Michael also took up the A / B testing to ensure the system they used the best interaction patterns for the specific users\' mental model of the system.\r\n<h3>Challanges</h3>\r\nIn large, complex projects for heavy IT systems, it is important to find the right extent of the design experience and both work at a high overall level for stakeholders and detailed level with the development team. Merging two large, complex IT systems used by many different audiences was another challange. And developing the right design patterns for widespread audiences.\r\n<h3>Experince</h3>\r\nWorking in distint sprints with a clear scum methodology to iterate through design proposals with project team and stakeholders.\r\n<h3>Methods and processes</h3>\r\nField studies, A / B testing scenarios, Wireframes, White board, pencil and paper, efficiency mapping, task analyzes.\r\n<h3>Conclusion</h3>\r\nWhen you have a close contact with end users and can do a lot of user testing it is a good way to know your work is on the right track. You can base all your work on facts instead of feelings.', 'Wasakredit', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '462-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-12-15 13:13:21', '2014-12-15 13:13:21', '', 462, 'http://www.mikaeleng.se/462-revision-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(497, 1, '2015-01-28 15:46:17', '2015-01-28 15:46:17', 'Medical Association knew that many of their members are surfing from phones and tablets. When the new site would be built on the target image was clear, it would work on tablet, cell phone and laptop. The site was therefore built with responsive web design.\n\nThe project was also carried out a restructuring of the content and a new graphical form was developed. The new website is built according to a completely new structure has been clarified main navigation where, for example, the number of choices in the main menu is limited down through user research and design principles. During the restructuring the prioritized target groups got a clear  linked to pages with information that is relevant for them. One of the Medical Association\'s goal with this site is that it will generate new members. Member Function has lifted and is now clearly on the homepage.\n<h3>Challanges</h3>\nGeting the company to understand the use of target groups to focus the website and help the users find their needs so they will get a better experience.\n<h3>Experience</h3>\nMaking complex information structures visual for target groups and stakeholders. Geting them to understand the models and working close with the target groups.\n<h3>Conclusion</h3>\nBuilding an understanding for information architecture and target groups will help your communication with stakeholder. Get your stakeholders to participate in the workshops with target groups and card sorting meetings will make your job easier.', 'Doctors union website', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '375-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 15:46:17', '2015-01-28 15:46:17', '', 375, 'http://www.mikaeleng.se/375-autosave-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(498, 1, '2014-12-15 13:24:33', '2014-12-15 13:24:33', 'Through workshops with SLF and interviews with employees at the company, I built a new information architecture of the site. I cleaned up the existing website and structured all the information created over a long period of time. In various workshops and interviews, I made an efficiency map and came up with different target groups. Focusing the website content on these target groups made the website more usable . I built a complex prototype to visualize the functionality, infrastructure and user experience at the new site. The prototype was then used in the design and development phase.\r\n<h3>Challanges</h3>\r\nGeting the company to understand the use of target groups to focus the website and help the users find their needs so they will get a better experience.\r\n<h3>Experience</h3>\r\nMaking complex information structures visual for target groups and stakeholders. Geting them to understand the models and working close with the target groups.\r\n<h3>Conclusion</h3>\r\nBuilding an understanding for information architecture and target groups will help your communication with stakeholder. Get your stakeholders to participate in the workshops with target groups and card sorting meetings will make your job easier.', 'SLF', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '375-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-12-15 13:24:33', '2014-12-15 13:24:33', '', 375, 'http://www.mikaeleng.se/375-revision-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
