(547, 1, '2015-01-02 22:17:31', '2015-01-02 22:17:31', 'Avito is Russia\'s largest web portal for classifieds. Avito wanted to create a better user experience for their service providers. Create a digital tool that their users could use as an everyday tool for their business. I did field studies on location in Russia and in-depth interviews and user tests with Russian users.\r\n<h3>Challanges</h3>\r\nTo understand and explore a new culture with different non-conscious interactions and mental models was one big challanges. Another challange was working with customers at a great distance and manage their expectations. To facilitate that I hade to give quick and detailed feedback as much as possible. I alos took on the role of UX Lead and worked with project planning, close customer contact, assign tasks and overall project management.\r\n<h3>Experience</h3>\r\nThe most important thing when working with international clients is to maintain frequent communication and pay extra attention to stakeholders expectations. While doing the interviewing users through an interpreter I must find clever ways to communicate without having to use the interpreter all the time. One can e.g. use scales to the user by pointing to a value on a scale answer a question.\r\n<h3>Methods and processes</h3>\r\nField studies, in-depth interviews, A/B tests, wireframes, Axure prototype, efficiency mapping, powerpoint presentations, documentation and communication to the board of directors.\r\n<h3>Conclusion</h3>\r\nKeep the line of communication open and be distint, cross-cultural barriers that may occur requires clear questions and answers for all communication, finding the right methods to extract as much information as possible.', 'Service provider tool', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '458-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-02 22:17:31', '2015-01-02 22:17:31', '', 458, 'http://www.mikaeleng.se/458-revision-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
