(618, 1, '2015-03-04 19:43:51', '2015-03-04 19:43:51', 'One of our customers asked us to develop a mobile application that would work on all mobile devices and systems. The application would be able to receive notifications from the client that they would push out to all units simultaneously. In the background there would be a CMS tool such as. WordPress.\r\n\r\nWe thought it was very exciting project and we started to look at what customer tasks and goals with the application. This application would primarily benefit as sales support in the field and helping sellers to get better support in the information of kundes deals.\r\n\r\nExcerpts from the production\r\n\r\n[BILD]\r\n\r\nWireframes\r\n\r\nWhen after many paper sketches came up with a proposal that resulted in these wireframes. Here are just a part of all that was. There were different versions on the grounds that it would be a web application so it worked on so many devices and systems as possible but still go fairly rapidly developing stälde the high demands for flexibility from us as a development team and the system itself.\r\n\r\nWe made the choice to proceed with an HTML5, CSS3 and JavaScript version so we could use WordPress in the background. I built a vertical mock-up and looked at some of the features essential to the system. after we started looking at the design and how we wanted to communicate our information.\r\n\r\nFlow charts and system architecture\r\n[BILD]\r\nAs the developer of the application, it was important to me that the underlying structure and communication worked so I put together various information flows to visualize for me and for the rest of the development team how information flowed through the system.', 'Mobile sales support tool', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '296-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-04 19:43:51', '2015-03-04 19:43:51', '', 296, 'http://www.mikaeleng.se/296-revision-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(619, 1, '2015-03-04 22:21:18', '2015-03-04 22:21:18', ' ', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '619', '', '', '2015-03-04 22:21:18', '2015-03-04 22:21:18', '', 0, 'http://www.mikaeleng.se/?p=619', 2, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(628, 1, '2016-04-23 13:58:07', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 'Auto Draft', '', 'auto-draft', 'open', 'closed', '', '', '', '', '2016-04-23 13:58:07', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 'http://www.mikaeleng.se/?p=628', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(622, 1, '2015-03-10 19:16:15', '2015-03-10 19:16:15', 'Wasa Kredit needed a new sales support tool for the different sales divisions which at the time had several different kinds of applications. I worked with Windows-specific interaction patterns and supported the rest of the development team with usability and information about user needs looked. I did several user interviews. I made continuous usability testing with users by producing a complex prototype in Axure and used the same tools to communicate interaction with the rest of the development team. I did A / B testing to ensure the system they used the best interaction patterns for the specific users\' mental model of the system.\r\n<h3>Challanges</h3>\r\nIn large, complex projects for heavy IT systems, it is important to find the right extent of the design experience and both work at a high overall level for stakeholders and detailed level with the development team. Merging two large, complex IT systems used by many different audiences was another challange. And developing the right design patterns for widespread audiences.\r\n<h3>Experince</h3>\r\nWorking in distint sprints with a clear scum methodology to iterate through design proposals with project team and stakeholders.\r\n<h3>Methods and processes</h3>\r\nField studies, A / B testing scenarios, Wireframes, White board, pencil and paper, efficiency mapping, task analyzes.\r\n<h3>Conclusion</h3>\r\nWhen you have a close contact with end users and can do a lot of user testing it is a good way to know your work is on the right track. You can base all your work on facts instead of feelings.', 'A new CRM tool', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '462-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-10 19:16:15', '2015-03-10 19:16:15', '', 462, 'http://www.mikaeleng.se/462-revision-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(623, 1, '2015-03-10 19:17:25', '2015-03-10 19:17:25', 'Cambio wanted to create a new public website that was more communicative and modern. The site would be responsive and adapt to diffenrent screen sizes. Using a variety of internal workshops with the client and all the stakeholders at Cambio to generate an efficiency map with the different target groups and their needs. With the target groups mapped out I did interviews with the four main target groups. I performed usability tests and A / B tests for various interactive work flows to create the best user experience. We used SCRUM as project methodology where I also accounted for all requirements specification and testing.', 'A modern company site', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '456-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-10 19:17:25', '2015-03-10 19:17:25', '', 456, 'http://www.mikaeleng.se/456-revision-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(625, 1, '2015-04-01 21:59:29', '2015-04-01 21:59:29', 'Cambio wanted to create a new public website that was more communicative and modern. The site would be responsive and adapt to diffenrent screen sizes. Using a variety of internal workshops with the client and all the stakeholders at Cambio to generate an efficiency map with the different target groups and their needs. With the target groups mapped out I did interviews with the four main target groups. I performed usability tests and A / B tests for various interactive work flows to create the best user experience. We used SCRUM as project methodology where I also accounted for all requirements specification and testing.', 'A responsive web site', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '456-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-04-01 21:59:29', '2015-04-01 21:59:29', '', 456, 'http://www.mikaeleng.se/456-revision-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(627, 1, '2015-07-23 19:19:00', '2015-07-23 19:19:00', 'SJ choose SharePoint 2013 Online for upgrading their intranet and the new requirements set by the company. I worked closely with various stakeholders in SJ\'s organisation in order to communicate the design and concept. My responsibility was to continuously inform these stakeholders throughout the project. As the project progressed, I took on the role of Product Owner and help the organization to establish requirements and prioritize the backlog created for the Scrum-based development team.\r\n<h3>Challanges:</h3>\r\nLarge company with many target groups. Complex environment that would work in a mobile  and an destop environment. I worked with mental models, attention to what you are working with and external factors from a security perspective.\r\n<h3>Experience:</h3>\r\nDistinct and regular communication to the business and personas / reference groups. Greater responsibility in terms of requirements, the Scrum process and production management.\r\n<h3>Methods and processes:</h3>\r\nField studies, usability testing, focus group analysis, personas, scenarios, board meeting presentation, documentation and communicating the internal information to the Board and management teams.\r\n<h3>Conclusion:</h3>\r\nAs a UX designer works with a variety of professional roles and stakeholders. It requires distinct and honest communication. Communicated in a way specific individual and professional roles can absorb it. You need to be flexible and give clear directions when the project is complex and demands are high.', 'Intranet', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '464-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-07-23 19:19:00', '2015-07-23 19:19:00', '', 464, 'http://www.mikaeleng.se/464-revision-v1', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
